On the morning of Feb. 29, a screenshot of a bctn document circulating on the Internet showed that bctn had announced that it was closing the company to initiate liquidation preparations. Bai Cheng travel is perhaps the first medium-sized travel company to close its doors after the industry was hit by the outbreak.

Screenshots show that in document 005 of 2020,100 trips said, "With the new coronavirus outbreak, tourism has been hit as never before and the industry has come to a standstill. Bai Cheng is also deeply affected, the capital can not maintain the company to continue to operate. To this end, the company held a shareholders'meeting, the management made a report, the shareholders'meeting decided to close the company and initiate liquidation preparations."

Baidu travel officials have not yet issued a response to the incident, but interface news confirmed to people close to Baidu travel.

Baicheng travel, whose full name is Beijing Baicheng International Travel Co. , Ltd. , mainly deals in online retail of outbound travel, mainly deals in visa services, and has extended its business to destination travel services. Its headquarter is located in Beijing, and in Shanghai, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Chengdu, Shenyang, Wuhan set up six branches. As of 2015,100 trips have served nearly 2 million people, according to the official website.

In April 2016,100-way travel was officially listed on the New Third Board. June 2019 News, hundreds of travel and other tourism enterprises from the new three board delisting delisting.

The reason for the delisting of the New Third Board is related to the company's strategic considerations, "because the new third board does not help small and medium-sized enterprises' fund-raising, and there are high annual management fees, " the person said

As for the shutdown and liquidation of 100 Cheng tourism, he analyzed that after 2016, the tide of Internet traffic dividends gradually receded, hot money in the capital market of the tourism industry decreased, and vicious competition in the visa industry was the main reason that 100 Cheng could not persist, the outbreak of the new coronavirus accelerated this process and led directly to funding problems.

From the external cause, Taobao, flying pig and other platforms on the small and medium-sized visa business fierce competition to affect the main business of Baicheng. "The threshold of the visa industry is very low. On the Tourism Retail Platform, visa merchants make quick money by taking advantage of low-priced customers and storing up traffic. This leads to vicious competition in the industry. For example, the phenomenon of vicious ticket-swiping is also common on the platform, which has an impact on formal enterprises such as Baicheng, " the person said, in the middle of 2019,100-way travel in Taobao, flying pigs and other online flow of access to the size of the trend, from the online platform to get traffic weakened, and the enterprise itself is not strong enough to wake up old users.

Perhaps as a result, BCH has increased its investment in destination business over the past few years.

In the first half of 2016,100 Cheng's visa business accounted for 60.9% of its revenue and 17.99% of its destination business. In the first half of 2017,117.60% year-on-year growth was recorded in 100 Cheng's destination business, accounting for 40.18% of its revenue structure, the percentage of visa business is 45.94% , and the percentage of destination business is 45.25% .

The company reported a smaller net loss for both 2017 and the second half of 2018. The half-yearly report for 2018 showed that the company made a net loss of 12.8564 million yuan, a decrease of 5.5273 million yuan and an increase of 22.86 percent in operating income of 284 million yuan. At the same time, the gross profit margin of 100-trip was 10.18% , down 1.11 percentage points from the same period last year.

However, although the destination business has brought a lot of revenue to the hundred journey, but take the loan as the main way in the destination business investment, has buried the hidden danger to the hundred journey traveling fund question.

"The company found that the combination of the visa and the destination business allowed us to cover labour costs, pay bonuses to employees and achieve a surplus in the accounts, but in fact the finance side did not synchronize the cost of funds to the business side into the destination business, such as accounting for loan interest, " the source said.

There is not enough cash to purchase the tourist goods of the destination, and the business of the destination needs more cash flow to sell the tourist products. For example, the purchase of ticket products, need to reach a certain scale of procurement, in order to get the lower market price of this product, to sell to make a profit. And the profit of travel product itself microblogs, some product gross profit rate even lower than the loan interest rate.

"So in the second half of 2018, the company gradually reduced the content of the destination, in April 2019 all cut, " said the source.

Coupled with 2018,2019 travel industry startup itself more difficult to raise money, 100 Cheng travel has not been easy.

The company raised $10 million in series a financing in 2008, with investors including stall capital (formerly Fidelity Asia) , Investor AB INVESTOR AB and others receiving a + round from Taishan Angel Investment in 2011, according to sky eyes, in 2014, Alibaba, CBC broadband capital 20 million US dollars B round of investment, 2015 from the Lake Shannan capital, flying pig capital and other 200 million yuan investment and Swiss capital strategic financing. According to the source, the company has had undisclosed financing since then, mostly from individuals.

Unexpectedly, during the Spring Festival, which was the peak season for outbound tourism, the new coronavirus outbreak led to the suspension of domestic tourism, the suspension of outbound tour groups, and in recent days, the epidemic has also become increasingly serious in other countries around the world, it has a direct impact on tourism enterprises.

"closing the doors is not necessarily a bad thing, " the source said in a final assessment, "I believe that Lao Zeng (founder and chairman of Baicheng Tourism) is not a loser. There is still time and energy, at least a good body to face it, and then can start again. "
